Title: 2-2 and 2-3 Intercombination Transitions in Be-like Ions
Authors: Yu.V.Ralchenko (Weizmann Institute of Science) and L.A.Vainshtein
  (Lebedev Physical Institute)
Categories: atom-ph physics.atom-ph
Comments: LaTeX, 4 pages, 2 Postscript figures, styles paper.sty and paper2.sty
  available from http://plasma-gate.weizmann.ac.il/~fnralch/paper/, to appear
  in the Proceedings of the 11th International Colloquium on UV and X-Ray
  Spectroscopy of Astrophysical and Laboratory Plasmas, Nagoya, Japan, 1994
DOI: 10.1103/PhysRevA.52.2449
\\
  We report here on calculation of probabilities of intercombination
transitions $2s^2$ $^1S_0$ - $2s2p$ $^3P_1$, $2s3p$ $^3P_1$ for Be-like ions
along the isoelectronic sequence for large range of $Z$. Our results obtained
with the $1/Z$ expansion method agree well with experimental data including the
recent ones.
